# Credential / signing file types — defense-in-depth. No current file
# matches these patterns; they're listed so a future `git add .` can't
# accidentally commit an Apple App Store Connect key (.p8), a
# provisioning profile (.mobileprovision / .provisionprofile), a PKCS-12
# bundle (.p12), a plain private key (.key / .pem), a certificate
# (.crt / .cer), or a Java keystore (.jks / .keystore) that someone
# happens to drop into the working tree while integrating CI.
*.pem
*.p12
*.p8
*.key
*.crt
*.cer
*.jks
*.keystore
*.mobileprovision
*.provisionprofile

# Local tooling / machine-specific state (belt-and-suspenders: these
# aren't tracked today, but listing them prevents a future `git add .`
# from accidentally committing Claude Code settings, Cloudflare Wrangler
# state, or machine-specific TestFlight export options.
.claude/
.wrangler/
ios/TestFlightExportOptions-local.plist
ios/background-assets/

# Node (for future website)
node_modules/
.next/
out/
dist/
.cache/

# Editor
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo

# Model assets (too big for git; downloaded via Background Assets at runtime)
*.gguf
*.mlx
*.safetensors
ios/Nod/Resources/Models/
